Christie Issues State of Emergency, Urges People to Leave New Jersey Shore

-- B y   E l i s e   Y o u n g
-- 
2011-08-25T16:37:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/christie-issues-state-of-emergency-urges-people-to-leave-new-jersey-shore.html
New Jersey Governor  Chris Christie 
signed a state of emergency order and urged people at the  Jersey
Shore  to leave voluntarily by mid-day tomorrow as Hurricane
Irene approaches the Northeast.  The governor, in a briefing with reporters, said he was
considering a mandatory evacuation of the Jersey Shore area.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elise Young in Trenton at 
